solution:
Subsets of {x, y, z}:
1. ∅
2. {x}
3. {y}
4. {z}
5. {x, y}
6. {x, z}
7. {y, z}
8. {x, y, z}

There are 8 subsets total (2³ = 8).

(a) {1, 2, 3} ⊕ {3, 4, 5}
Elements in first only: {1, 2}
Elements in second only: {4, 5}
Union: {1, 2, 4, 5}

(b) Proof:
x ∈ A ⊕ B 
⟺ (x ∈ A ∨ x ∈ B) ∧ ¬(x ∈ A ∧ x ∈ B)  [Def of XOR]
⟺ (x ∈ A ∧ x ∉ B) ∨ (x ∈ B ∧ x ∉ A)   [Logical equivalence]
⟺ x ∈ (A - B) ∨ x ∈ (B - A)           [Def of Set Difference]
⟺ x ∈ (A - B) ∪ (B - A)               [Def of Union]

description:
Let S = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}. Definition: A partition is a collection of non-empty disjoint subsets whose union is S.
Which of the following are valid partitions of S?
(a) {{1, 2}, {3, 4, 5}, {6}}
(b) {{1, 2, 3}, {3, 4, 5, 6}}
(c) {{1, 2}, {4, 5, 6}}

