R⁻¹ = {(y,x) | x < y}
Switching variables to standard form: {(a,b) | b < a}, which is simply {(a,b) | a > b}.

So the inverse of "less than" is "greater than".

1 maps to 2 via R. 2 maps to a via S. -> (1,a)
2 maps to 3 via R. 3 maps to b via S. -> (2,b)

S ∘ R = {(1,a), (2,b)}

